{"tid":690560,"cid":6,"subCid":0,"title":"波蘭正選中堅因為練習窩利射門令膊頭受傷或缺席世界盃","createTime":"2018-06-05T03:46:53.000Z","updateTime":"2018-06-11T15:07:16.000Z","uid":55981,"like":1,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":29,"replies":[{"pid":"4b1956a7325962f562b90fef6fcbc8b4ab5ef8ae","tid":690560,"uid":55981,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-06-05T03:46:53.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://static.independent.co.uk/s3fs-public/thumbnails/image/2016/11/22/22/glik.jpg?w968h681\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.independent.co.uk%2Fs3fs-public%2Fthumbnails%2Fimage%2F2016%2F11%2F22%2F22%2Fglik.jpg%3Fw968h681&h=6347e07f&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\nOne of Poland's key players, defender Kamil Glik, could miss the World Cup after injuring himself attempting a bicycle kick in training. <br />\n<br />\nThe robust Monaco centre-back was supposed to be the rock on which Adam Nawalka's Polish side were built at Russia 2018, but a cruel twist of fate may yet rob him of the chance to play at the World Cup. <br />\n<br />\nGlik was taken to hospital where a number of tests were carried out on his shoulder. With such a lack of clarity over his situation and with the squad submission deadline on Monday, Nawalka included Glik in his squad but now faces a race against time to be fit for Poland's opener against Senegal on June 19."},{"pid":"cb49e890be76969b57a259c97a05c90574f0fbd2","tid":690560,"uid":96941,"like":8,"dislike":2,"score":6,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-06-05T03:59:55.000Z","msg":"好心訓練就咪咁搏喇<br />\n而家柒到冇眼睇<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"4510941765f32e44f055aa160b19971eec8be3c6","tid":690560,"uid":9813,"like":4,"dislike":0,"score":4,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-06-05T04:01:01.000Z","msg":"陰鳩公<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/